A 68-year-old Gabre Gesu Lemita is among 5,488 candidates sitting KCPE in Marsabit. Gabre is a private candidate at Moyale Township Adult centre. He has nine children and 12 grandchildren. "I'm optimistic that I will proceed to secondary school and later join college to pursue my dream of education," Gabre said on Tuesday. The county has 131 centres. A total of 3,419 boys are sitting the exams compared to 2,069 girls. Click here for the latest political news   